title: Grateful Dead Live at The Omni on 1991-04-04
lineage: Master Cassettes (Maxell MX-S 90) Tascam 112MKII -> Korg MR-1, 1bit 2.8MHz -> USB -> Korg Audio Gate Software 24bit 48KHz -> Wave Lab 6.0 w/UAD -> R8brain for 16bit 44.1KHz sample rate conversion -> Traders Little Helper flac8 -> Tag With Tag & Rename
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll, Feel Like A Stranger, They Love Each Other, Walkin' Blues, Ramble On Rose, Memphis Blues, High Time, Promised Land

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Standing On the Moon-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Awesome quality! These new Holtz recordings are astounding!  I just listened to 4/3 last night, am looking forward to boogieing to this one while cleaning house today. :-)

Who IS that fool at the beginning screaming, "Will you offer me a tape to shut up?" >:-(
